export function createDefaultInstructionsMarkdown() {
    return [
        '# QDD Instructions',
        '',
        '## Quick Reference',
        '',
        '### Truth Sources',
        '',
        '- `contract.yaml` - research theme, scope, and authority mode',
        '- `evolution.yaml` - sparse study history plus the current open/resolved boundary map',
        '- `context/resources.md` - default human-readable project resources',
        '- `context/memory/STUDY-XXX.md` - per-study memory written during closure',
        '- other `context/*.md` and `context/*.yaml` files - optional reusable context sidecars',
        '- `.qdd/layer-policy.yaml` - command -> role mapping and role-level default skills',
        '- `.qdd/skills-catalog.json` - derived machine-readable index of executor problem-level skills',
        '- `artifacts/data/` - project-local dataset entrypoints and promoted reusable data files',
        '- `domain-skills/` - QDD-root domain skill library used to validate task skill IDs',
        '- `.codex/skills/qdd/` - project-local workflow skill surface for Codex-compatible bootstrap installs',
        '- `.claude/skills/qdd/` - mirrored workflow skill surface for Claude-compatible bootstrap installs',
        '- `studies/STUDY-XXX/study.md` - bounded study definition',
        '- `studies/STUDY-XXX/tasks/TASK-XXX.md` - evidence-producing task definition',
        '- `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/artifact-candidates.yaml` - explicit promotion list for reusable study outputs',
        '- `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/public_data_request.yaml` - thin planning-to-apply handoff for external public dataset search and download',
        '- `artifacts/index.yaml` - reusable artifact registry',
        '- `research-map.html` - derived project-local study/boundary visualization report',
        '',
        '### Installed Workflow Surfaces',
        '',
        '- `qdd-start` - onboard project context, dataset links, and local skills before the first study',
        '- `qdd-propose` - frame one bounded study from a human-supplied question or hypothesis',
        '- `qdd-explore` - stress-test the study and converge to a resource-supported plan',
        '- `qdd-apply` - execute within the active study until it reaches a decision point',
        '- `qdd-close` - validate, synthesize, carry forward stable context, and close the study',
        '- `qdd-conclude` - synthesize a mature project, align a detailed manuscript story, then complete a Nature-style TeX draft',
        '',
        '### CLI Checkpoints',
        '',
        '- `qdd init` - install the scaffold and bootstrap surfaces; do not recreate them manually',
        '- `qdd status --json` - inspect the project-level dashboard before high-level decisions',
        '- `qdd instructions PROJECT --command qdd-start --json` - inspect project onboarding bounds before changing shared context',
        '- `qdd instructions <id> --command <qdd-...> --json` - use authoritative role-aware bounds before editing a study or task',
        '- `qdd context --json` - inspect reusable project context',
        '- `qdd artifacts:list --json` - inspect reusable outputs before regenerating work',
        '- `qdd skills suggest --domain <domain> --stage <stage> --tag <tag> --json` - propose problem-level executor skills during planning',
        '- `qdd validate --json` - run before closure or a high-confidence handoff',
        '- `research-map.html` - derived project-local HTML map refreshed by init and close',
        '',
        '## Mode Contract',
        '',
        '### Shared Rules',
        '',
        '- Treat `contract.yaml.mode` as the authority signal for workflow behavior.',
        '- Treat `evolution.yaml` as the sparse project-state truth source for closed studies and current boundaries.',
        '- Treat YAML frontmatter as machine-readable truth and Markdown sections as execution guidance.',
        '- `study.md` and `task.md` are the template-constrained artifacts in this workflow slice.',
        '- Workflow prompts such as `qdd-propose`, `qdd-explore`, `qdd-apply`, `qdd-close`, and `qdd-conclude` guide reasoning and behavior; they are not rigid output schemas.',
        '- Use `.qdd/layer-policy.yaml` to map commands to roles and provide role-level default skills.',
        '- Only reference domain task skills that exist under the QDD root `domain-skills/` library.',
        '- Only write task skills that also qualify as executor problem-level skills in `.qdd/skills-catalog.json`.',
        '- Treat `thesis/*` as thesis-manager planning skills and `brain/*` as study-brain planning skills; neither belongs in task `skills:`.',
        '- Keep task frontmatter `skills:` and the body `## Skills` section identical.',
        '- Only write evidence-backed, cross-study reusable knowledge into `context/` resources.',
        '- Treat `context/resources.md` as the default durable project memory for data resources, runtime environments, compute capability, and analyst preferences.',
        '- Before running Python, R, conda, or other analysis commands, check `context/resources.md` and prefer the declared project environment; if you do not use it, state why.',
        '- Keep study narrative, reflections, and carry-forward hints in `context/memory/STUDY-XXX.md`, not in `evolution.yaml`.',
        '',
        '### start',
        '',
        '1. Use `qdd instructions PROJECT --command qdd-start --json` before editing shared project context.',
        '2. Fill `contract.yaml` and `context/resources.md` with real project facts, and only add durable analyst preferences when they are stable enough to bias later work.',
        '3. Run best-effort CPU-core and basic GPU availability checks, then write only a concise capability summary into `context/resources.md`.',
        '4. Do not record local executable paths, home directories, usernames, raw environment variable values, API keys, tokens, or private environment names in `context/resources.md`.',
        '5. If the user declared preferred Python/R/conda environments, record them in portable terms and do not overwrite them unless they are demonstrably wrong or unavailable.',
        '6. Add project dataset entrypoints under `artifacts/data/` using symlinks instead of copying raw data.',
        '7. Treat the QDD root `domain-skills/` library as the domain-skill validation inventory, and `.claude/.codex` local skill trees as workflow bootstrap surfaces only.',
        '8. Do not try to pre-govern the whole project frontier here. Let study-level propose/explore/close update `evolution.yaml` later.',
        '9. Refresh or inspect `.qdd/skills-catalog.json` if local problem-level skills changed.',
        '10. Stop when the project is ready for the first `qdd-propose` pass.',
        '',
        '### human',
        '',
        '- Humans own study-level direction and closure judgment.',
        '- `qdd-start` collects and structures project facts, but must not invent them.',
        '- `qdd-propose` writes the first-pass `study + task graph` directly when the direction is actionable.',
        '- `qdd-explore` is discussion-first and confirmation-gated before modifying study/task artifacts.',
        '- `qdd-apply` executes the current approved study/task set and keeps advancing inside the same study until the study becomes judgeable, blocked, or truly needs study-level replanning.',
        '- `qdd-close` still requires human scientific judgment in human mode, but once closure is justified and preflight passes, the CLI should execute directly without a second manual confirmation gate.',
        '',
        '### assist',
        '',
        '- Follow the same artifact authority boundaries as `human` mode.',
        '- `qdd-start` may draft more structure, but still depends on human-supplied project facts.',
        '- You may draft more concrete edits, task shapes, and closure reasoning, but still wait for confirmation before changing study/task artifacts in `qdd-explore` or finalizing closure.',
        '',
        '### auto',
        '',
        '- `qdd-start` may structure provided facts directly, but must not fabricate missing project context.',
        '- Proceed directly when the project and study context are sufficient.',
        '- `qdd-explore` is optional in auto mode; do not require a separate explore stop if the study is already actionable.',
        '- Keep plan growth minimal and stay inside the current study boundary.',
        '',
        '## Workflow',
        '',
        '### Start',
        '',
        '1. If the project is not initialized, run `qdd init` first.',
        '2. Read `qdd status --json` and `qdd instructions PROJECT --command qdd-start --json`.',
        '3. Update `contract.yaml` and `context/resources.md` with the real research theme, biological background, data availability, safe runtime/compute capability summary, and any durable analyst preferences worth carrying across studies.',
        '4. Keep runtime facts portable: summarize CPU cores and basic GPU availability, but never persist personal paths, private environment names, credentials, or raw environment variable values.',
        '5. Create or refresh dataset entrypoints under `artifacts/data/` using symlinks.',
        '6. Keep project-owned workflow skills under the local `qdd/` bootstrap surface and do not reference domain skills missing from the central `domain-skills/` library as if they already exist.',
        '',
        '### Propose',
        '',
        '1. If the project is not initialized, run `qdd init` first.',
        '2. If project context is still placeholder-level, complete `qdd-start` first.',
        '3. Read `qdd status --json` and, when useful, `qdd context --json` and `qdd artifacts:list --json`.',
        '4. Read `context/resources.md`, `evolution.yaml`, and recent `context/memory/*.md` before planning so the next study stays grounded in prior evidence and declared resources.',
        '5. In human mode, preserve the user\'s scientific intent as the highest semantic authority. Treat next-question suggestions from prior closure only as candidates.',
        '6. Create or refresh one bounded `study.md` and a small first-pass `TASK-XXX.md` graph, usually 2-4 tasks.',
        '7. Use the study/task templates directly and rewrite placeholders into concrete first-pass content.',
        '8. Treat `target_boundaries` as descriptive links to the current open boundaries this study will clarify, not as a score-optimization target.',
        '9. Use study-brain skills plus `qdd skills suggest ... --json` during planning when problem-level skill selection matters.',
        '10. Only write task skills that already exist under the central `domain-skills/` library and appear in `.qdd/skills-catalog.json`.',
        '11. Never write `qdd/*` workflow skills or `thesis/*` or `brain/*` planning skills into task `skills:`.',
        '12. If a study depends on external public datasets, decide that during planning: either choose a small selected target set and record it in studies/STUDY-XXX/output/public_data_request.yaml, or record a bounded blocker.',
        '12a. If a study only needs lightweight public-data capture such as markers, ligand-receptor pairs, GEO candidate tables, or PubMed evidence tables, keep the bounded search intent in the task and materialize the chosen local CSV/TSV outputs directly instead of creating public_data_request.yaml.',
        '13. Do not leave obvious first-pass evidence gaps for apply to invent later.',
        '14. Do not turn propose into a long debate; later critique belongs in `qdd-explore`.',
        '',
        '### Explore',
        '',
        '1. Run `qdd instructions STUDY-XXX --command qdd-explore --json` before reshaping a study.',
        '2. Explore only options that remain relevant to the active study question and current task set.',
        '2a. Read `evolution.yaml` and recent `context/memory/*.md` before changing study direction so discussion stays grounded in prior evidence.',
        '3. Read `context/resources.md` when data availability, preferred environments, or reusable analyst preferences could affect the discussion.',
        '4. In `human` and `assist` mode, discuss and refine first; do not modify study/task files until the user confirms.',
        '5. Use study-brain heuristics and `qdd skills suggest ... --json` when task-level problem-skill choice is uncertain.',
        '5a. When external public data may be needed, use planning to decide whether to create a public-data task at all; do not force one when local resources are already sufficient.',
        '5b. Keep dataset-style public-data acquisition separate from lighter public-data capture tasks; only the dataset path should depend on public_data_request.yaml.',
        '6. Converge to a resource-supported plan: worth doing, feasible now, blockers, evidence plan, and task shape.',
        '7. If `target_boundaries` no longer match the study question, rewrite them as descriptive current-open links rather than trying to preserve stale structure.',
        '8. Stop when the study is executable, explicitly blocked, or ready for approved edits.',
        '',
        '### Apply',
        '',
        '1. Treat the study as the execution unit.',
        '1a. Read project context and recent study memory for alignment when needed, but do not mutate project-level evolution state during apply.',
        '2. Run `qdd instructions STUDY-XXX --command qdd-apply --json` first, then `qdd instructions TASK-XXX --command qdd-apply --json` for the current approved task set.',
        '3. Read `context/resources.md` before running Python, R, conda, or other analysis commands; prefer the declared project environment, and if you do not use it, state why.',
        '4. If a task declares missing domain skills, hard-block execution until the skill exists under the central `domain-skills/` library or the task is rewritten.',
        '5. Do not reopen broad catalog search during apply; consume only the task-local problem-level skill bundle.',
        '5a. Do not reopen broad public-dataset search during apply; if a dataset-style public-data task exists, consume only the already selected dataset targets recorded during planning.',
        '5b. Lightweight public-data tasks may execute a bounded source search already written into the task, but they must materialize the chosen local CSV/TSV outputs directly and must not invent a new managed YAML handoff.',
        '6. Rewrite the weak task checklist scaffold into task-specific executable steps before or during execution.',
        '7. Update study and task Markdown directly while the work progresses.',
        '8. Package local evidence under `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/{data,code,figures,tables,reports}/` when those output types are produced.',
        '9. Record promotion-worthy outputs in `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/artifact-candidates.yaml`; include `task_id` whenever one task clearly produced the output.',
        '9a. When a task runs substantive analysis code, preserve the main executed script in `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/code/` and normally record it as a `type: code` candidate unless it is directly registered.',
        '9b. When a task produces the final processed h5ad used as a downstream starting point, preserve that final kept object in `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/data/` rather than leaving it only in scratch space.',
        '9c. When a task produces reusable summary matrices or comparison CSV/TSV outputs, preserve them under `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/tables/` and record them as `type: table` candidates when they are promotion-worthy.',
        '10. Set each completed task\'s `promotion_status` explicitly to `none`, `candidate-recorded`, or `registered`; completed tasks must not remain `pending`.',
        '11. Use `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/tmp/` only as scratch space and package final data/code/figures/tables/reports back into canonical study output directories before task completion.',
        '12. Treat slow clustering, UMAP, integration, and large h5ad processing as normal long-running work unless there is explicit evidence of failure.',
        '13. Finishing one task does not end apply; keep moving through the planned task graph while the next study-local step is clear.',
        '14. Continue until the study reaches a decision point, explicit blocker, or a true study-level replanning need that should return to `qdd-explore`.',
        '',
        '### Close',
        '',
        '1. Run `qdd validate --json` before closure or handoff.',
        '2. Read `context/resources.md` before deciding what stable data, environment, or analyst-preference context should carry forward.',
        '3. Synthesize evidence from the study, tasks, outputs, and registered artifacts.',
        '4. Refuse closure while any completed task still has `promotion_status: pending`.',
        '5. Refuse closure while non-canonical top-level study output material still remains unpackaged.',
        '6. Refuse closure when artifact candidates still point into `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/tmp/` or other scratch-only paths.',
        '7. Register any missing reusable outputs listed in `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/artifact-candidates.yaml` before closure.',
        '8. Allow closure when the study has enough evidence to confirm, refine, pivot, or dissolve the current question.',
        '9. Read `qdd instructions STUDY-XXX --command qdd-close --json` so closure runs under the thesis-manager role rather than only the study-facing surface.',
        '10. Use `thesis/frontier-planning` to decide whether the project frontier should continue, stop, or exceptionally need human review.',
        '11. If close preflight passes, run `qdd close-study` directly; do not wait for a second confirmation gate.',
        '12. Record one sparse study event in `evolution.yaml`: question, kind, resolved boundaries, opened boundaries, and candidate next questions.',
        '13. Keep only 1-3 next candidates and include expected signal plus strategy in candidate text or memory.',
        '14. Write one `context/memory/STUDY-XXX.md` file during closure so later agents can read what actually happened.',
        '15. Refresh `research-map.html` after closure.',
        '16. Update stable `context/` resources directly when the evidence is reusable across studies.',
        '17. Successful close should clean heavy scratch leftovers under `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/tmp/` while preserving final packaged truth.',
        '18. Suggest next studies, but do not create them automatically.',
        '',
        '## Validation Checklist',
        '',
        '- Did you call `qdd status --json` before making high-level project judgments?',
        '- Did you inspect `evolution.yaml` and recent `context/memory/*.md` before planning or closure decisions that depend on prior project state?',
        '- Did you call `qdd instructions PROJECT --command qdd-start --json` before changing shared project context or dataset entrypoints?',
        '- Did you call `qdd instructions <id> --command <qdd-...> --json` before editing an existing study or task?',
        '- Did you preserve YAML frontmatter at the top of every managed Markdown file?',
        '- Did project dataset entrypoints under `artifacts/data/` use symlinks instead of copied raw data when they are shared resources rather than promoted artifacts?',
        '- Did every task-level skill reference resolve under the QDD root `domain-skills/` library?',
        '- Did every task-level skill list avoid `qdd/*` workflow skills and `thesis/*` or `brain/*` planning skills?',
        '- Did every task-level skill reference correspond to a cataloged executor problem-level skill?',
        '- Did task frontmatter `skills:` stay identical to the body `## Skills` section?',
        '- Did you keep one bounded question per study?',
        '- Did you keep `study.md` and `task.md` as the only template-constrained artifacts?',
        '- Did `qdd-propose` create a concrete first-pass study and task graph rather than one vague starter task?',
        '- Did each completed task leave `promotion_status` in `none`, `candidate-recorded`, or `registered` rather than `pending`?',
        '- Did final study outputs get packaged back into `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/{data,code,figures,tables,reports}/` instead of remaining as non-canonical top-level leftovers?',
        '- Did `qdd-explore` stay discussion-first in `human` and `assist` mode?',
        '- Did `qdd-apply` execute through the current study/task graph rather than stopping after one task or defaulting to plan redesign?',
        '- Did you rewrite the weak task checklist scaffold into task-specific executable steps?',
        '- Did substantive analyses leave behind readable scripts in `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/code/`?',
        '- Did visual claims leave behind key figures in `studies/STUDY-XXX/output/figures/` or explicitly state why no figure was needed?',
        '- Did promoted outputs come from the explicit study candidate list rather than blind output scanning?',
        '- Did every reusable output get registered with explicit provenance, including `task_id` when one task clearly produced it?',
        '- Did `qdd-close` allow explicit refinement/pivot/dissolution closure when the question materially advanced, instead of forcing fake confirmation?',
        '- Did closure keep `evolution.yaml` sparse and move narrative into `context/memory/STUDY-XXX.md`?',
        '- Did you keep context updates stable, evidence-backed, and reusable across studies?',
        '',
        '## Advanced Notes',
        '',
        '- Use `refinement`, `confirmation`, `pivot`, or `dissolution` when recording a closed study event.',
        '- `context/` is an open context directory; `context/resources.md` is the default readable entrypoint for project facts and durable preferences, and YAML remains optional for structured sidecars.',
        '- `domain-skills/` is the domain-skill validation inventory, while `.codex/skills/qdd/` and `.claude/skills/qdd/` are local workflow bootstrap surfaces.',
        '- `.qdd/layer-policy.yaml` maps workflow commands onto `thesis-manager`, `study-brain`, or `executor` and may attach role-level default skills.',
        '- `artifacts/data/` is the shared data surface; files there are not formal artifacts unless they are registered in `artifacts/index.yaml`.',
        '- `qdd-explore` may discuss alternatives, but it must return to the active study question before it ends.',
        '- In this slice, workflow prompt source may live in repo-local Markdown files used by the bootstrap generator.',
        '- The default task checklist scaffold is intentionally weak and should be rewritten for the real task.',
        '- `artifact-candidates.yaml` is the explicit promotion boundary between local study outputs and reusable artifacts.',
        '- `evolution.yaml` is the sparse project map, while `context/memory/*.md` carries study-level narrative and reflection.',
        '- In artifact candidates, `task_id` records provenance, while `scope` records reuse surface; do not conflate them.',
        '- `qdd boundaries --json` and `qdd boundaries render ...` remain optional compatibility views derived from `evolution.yaml`; they are not project truth sources.',
        '- There is no separate `qdd-project` wrapper in this slice.',
        '- There is no assist-mode planner, learned-rules engine, or automatic next-study creation yet.',
        '',
    ].join('\n');
}
